This article is a readout of a meeting held by the White House Office of the Vice President regarding a potential threat occurring in or emanating from the Arabian Peninsula. The President instructed his National Security team to take appropriate steps to protect the American people. Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, Lisa Monaco, held regular meetings with relevant members of the interagency throughout the week. National Security Advisor Rice chaired a meeting with the Principals Committee to further review the situation and discuss follow-up actions. The President received frequent briefings on all aspects of the potential threat and our preparedness measures. Attendees at the meeting included White House Chief of Staff Denis McDonough, Secretary of State John Kerry, Secretary of Defense Chuck Hagel, and other top officials from various government agencies.